      • spendMoney

        public boolean spendMoney(int amt)
        Spends the amount given if the Trainer has it. If the Trainer has insufficient funds, nothing happens and returns false.
        Parameters:
        amt - Amount of money to spend.
        Returns:
        True if the Trainer spent it successfully. Otherwise, false.

      • receiveMoney

        public void receiveMoney(int amt)
        Adds money to the Trainer's wallet. Will not do anything if value input is negative. To take away money, use Trainer.spendMoney(int). To zero money, use Trainer.spendMoney(Trainer.getMoney()).
        Parameters:
        amt - Amount of money to give to the Trainer.

      • goSouth

        Moves the player south if a valid location. Location is based on Multi-Dimensional Array Map: [x][y] +x goes South Will return 'f' and automatically switch maps when moved onto a goal spot.
        Returns:
        If successful, char at new location. Otherwise, '\0'.

      • debuffPokemon

        public void debuffPokemon(int index)
        Debuffs a specific pokemon based on index. Pokemon Index begins at 1. Pokemon Index defined in this way because most menus start at 1.
        Parameters:
        index - Index of the Pokemon (Starting from 1)

      • getPokemon

        public Pokemon getPokemon(int index)
        Gets the Pokemon based on it's index number. Pokemon Index begins at 1. Pokemon Index defined in this way because most menus start at 1. Returns null with an invalid index.
        Parameters:
        index - Index of the Pokemon (Starting from 1)
        Returns:
        Pokemon if a valid index is provided. Otherwise, null.
